16/09/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Nine people in a minibus were killed by an explosion in Kurdish-dominated southeastern Turkey on Thursday (September 16th); four others were injured, according to Hakkari Governor Muammer Turker. 
Some sources say the minibus hit a landmine, while others suggest the bomb blew up inside the vehicle, which reportedly was travelling between the villages of Durankaya and Gecitli. 
(CNN Turk, BBC, Reuters, AP, NTV, Dogan, Cihan, Hurriyet - 16/09/10)
